WEBVTT

00:05.768 --> 00:07.201
Ted, what are you doing?

00:07.433 --> 00:08.658
Band practice.

00:09.259 --> 00:10.149
What band?

00:10.323 --> 00:11.548
Peons assemble!

00:12.490 --> 00:15.461
They have to stay within earshot,
it's in the band code.

00:15.692 --> 00:18.014
Wow, Ted,
it's kind of like you're their leader.

00:18.097 --> 00:19.232
Peons disperse!

00:21.352 --> 00:22.589
Peons assemble!

00:22.982 --> 00:24.316
Enough of the horse play!

00:24.399 --> 00:26.936
Now we need to practice,
and I can't have you winded.

00:27.156 --> 00:29.909
Now we've only got one shot
to convince Dr. Cox

00:29.992 --> 00:32.430
to let us sing for the sick kids
in pediatrics.

00:32.910 --> 00:33.790
One, two.

00:34.640 --> 00:36.213
[Blue Oyster Cult - Don't Fear The Reaper]

00:37.817 --> 00:41.482
# All our times have come,

00:44.295 --> 00:46.488
# Seasons don't fear the Reaper,

00:46.571 --> 00:48.079
Oh boy, good luck with that.

00:48.162 --> 00:49.952
<i>As wrong as it was
to serenade sick kids</i>

00:50.035 --> 00:51.896
<i>with a song about
the upside of death,</i>

00:51.979 --> 00:54.681
<i>it was perfect for my walk
to Dr. Cox's office.</i>

00:54.866 --> 00:57.852
<i>Yep, it was terrifying
going up against the new chief.</i>

00:58.376 --> 01:01.335
Perry, for the last time, we need
more negative pressure rooms

01:01.370 --> 01:02.766
in the infectious diseases ward.

01:04.075 --> 01:05.644
Huh, I didn't hear you knock.

01:05.920 --> 01:07.088
The door was open.

01:07.192 --> 01:10.282
Then go outside,
close the door, and knock.

01:10.539 --> 01:11.901
No, you're just going to lock it.

01:12.162 --> 01:12.872
No, I won't.

01:13.057 --> 01:14.722
You know I've been burned before.

01:14.918 --> 01:15.760
Believe in me.

01:15.843 --> 01:18.100
- New chapter?
- New chapter.

01:20.413 --> 01:21.785
New chapter!

01:24.413 --> 01:25.163
Perry Cox.

01:25.246 --> 01:26.681
<i>We still need those rooms.</i>

01:26.800 --> 01:28.908
And you sir, are a liar.

01:28.960 --> 01:30.857
There is no money in the budget.

01:30.880 --> 01:33.556
And while you're delivering
bad news, please tell Ted

01:33.639 --> 01:35.716
that he can't <i>sing in pediatrics.</i>

01:35.884 --> 01:38.557
A cappella music is,
how to put this delicately...

01:39.457 --> 01:40.377
ear rape.

01:42.759 --> 01:43.845
Guys, guys, guys!

01:44.286 --> 01:45.225
He said no.

01:45.393 --> 01:46.540
Oh man!

01:46.625 --> 01:49.708
Well maybe, he'll let us sing
for the people in the burn ward.

01:49.791 --> 01:50.809
No, I asked.

01:50.892 --> 01:53.060
He said they're already
in enough pain.

01:53.540 --> 01:55.979
Besides, Teddy, hospital already
has someone who sings to the kids.

01:56.170 --> 01:56.879
Who?

01:58.155 --> 02:01.225
# One day
# The moon got tired of being

02:01.424 --> 02:02.729
# Up in the sky

02:02.906 --> 02:05.311
# He wandered
# Down through the starlight

02:05.362 --> 02:08.531
# And landed on the ocean side
# <i>And he smiled while...</i>

02:08.902 --> 02:10.189
That's a cute song.

02:10.732 --> 02:11.808
It's not cute.

02:12.571 --> 02:13.565
It's beautiful.

02:13.566 --> 02:15.625
# His swim trunks and snorkel
# And guess what

02:16.028 --> 02:17.168
<i># Mr. Moon swam</i>

02:18.197 --> 02:21.027
Good news, Cox just added
two new negative pressure rooms.

02:21.110 --> 02:22.521
Great job wearing him down.

02:22.604 --> 02:25.821
<i>But still, with Dr. Cox,
winning has ramifications.</i>

02:25.804 --> 02:29.464
Janice, you have one ugly baby.
Seriously.

02:29.532 --> 02:32.410
Did you actually teach your son
to be mean to a baby?

02:32.493 --> 02:35.818
Not just any baby,
but your baby.

02:35.901 --> 02:37.045
Come here, Jackie Boy!

02:37.614 --> 02:39.471
We're going to get
10,000 jelly beans.

02:40.315 --> 02:41.518
I love you so much.

02:44.040 --> 02:45.727
They can both be so hurtful.

